    take — built by backgrounding a stack of <code class="mono" style="background: var(--bg-deep); padding: 1px 6px; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--live); font-size: 0.9rem;">npx vibes-diy generate</code> calls
    and waiting. No wrapper function needed. The CLI's defaults are fine.
  </p>

  <div class="cmd">
    <span class="c"># cluster/_run.sh — fire ten in parallel, wait for them all</span><br/>
    npx vibes-diy generate <span class="s">"Pizza-trivia study app..."</span> &amp;<br/>
    npx vibes-diy generate <span class="s">"Reunite lonely socks after laundry..."</span> &amp;<br/>
